cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.COMPU

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with quantization of information (signature selection) and feedback of limited information, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of a signature quantization scheme in a CDMA network, which is a networking and internet architecture topic. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper analyzes the performance of a signature quantization scheme in a network, which can be considered a social and information network. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper considers the effect of fading on the performance of the signature quantization scheme, which is a multimedia topic as fading can affect the quality of multimedia transmission. 
5. cs.COMPU (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses mathematical analysis to derive the SINR in a large system limit, which can be considered a computational engineering topic.
